MALGRÉ TOUT.
(Nevertheless) A love story.
Well, here they are. My upcoming book is about this two guys and their love story. ( a non usual one, by the way )
They have been in my mind and heart for the last two years and if everything goes as it should, they will be in your  book store the next fall. So far, it's been an amazing trip. Wish me luck for the rest! 
I'll keep you posted with more details, thank you so much!
Cheers!

Oxford.
Ok, this is what I call a “parenting piece”. Is a drawing done while fathering time: While I put my son to sleep, I wait in the dark until he is 100% asleep, and a homework session with my daughter, sitting next to her watching her finish ( She didn’t really need me, just wanted me around. She is way much smart than me ).
And I did a kind of Vogue piece because my wife loves fashion pictures.
This is my of being a family man.

Always the strongest person in the room.
This piece is a panel of the beginning of the graphic novel I am working on, and has a bit of history about writing and editing.

In the first draft, this was a sequence with a mother-daughter discussion, in a quite theatrical scene. There is almost no physical action, only two women talking each other.

When I sent it to my editor @ryun_reuchamps,  she said: "I love the sequence and the relationship between these two. I would like you to go a little further.
It was good news / bad news.
'Further' how?

I had the impression that they said what they had to say how it was, in a discussion "protected in his trench". How could I make them both leave their protection at the same time?

Put them in danger, I thought.
Outside your comfort zone.
And the granddaughter comes to my mind.
A new generation to turn everything upside down.

So I rewrote the scene when the girl literally invades her privacy with her confidence.
And it worked! The sequence is much better now, thanks to the vision of my editor.
(This is one of the best skills an editor can have:  taste plus vision)

The motto "putting them in danger" became a rule for the entire script.

Writing this book is a great adventure, full of friends and people who help me.
I hope to tell you more about it!
Thank you all :) J.

#graphicnovel #artoninstagram #art #womenempowerment #characterdesign #writing #writing #women

The last walk of the year.
2019 it's been a pretty tough year for me and people I love. Quite shitty, to be honest.
I keep the good moments as jewels in the middle of a mud windy storm. 
But If I take a bigger picture, the decade has ben an amazing journey I would never had imagined. 
I'm not an optimistic guy anymore, but I haven't completely lost my hope in a better future ( Even if I see bigots and nazis and climate crises ver-where.) So let's keep walking guys. Just keep walking.
Thank you to all persons that shared me this last year; You make my life much more happier. 
Be a bit with yourself tonight, tell the people you love that you love them, clean your own rubbish, and rest well; A new decade starts tomorrow. 
See  you on the other side.
Kisses, 
J.  #BD #bandedessinée #comicbook #illustration #characterdesingn #artistsoninstagram #december #2020 #2019 #lovequotes #couples #beautiful

The puppies.
As I write my next book and work on it, I realise that you can picture a strong woman just removing a man from a powerful position and putting your female character on the place. We all are so used to see men in that pictures that by only giving a woman the place,the image takes an entire different meaning. I think it's sad and funny at the same time. So I decided to torture a bit the guys on the meeting insinuating that the woman in office is not going to agree with them at all.

“Melancholy people, like you, are those who feel life is for the others, not them.”
My therapist. 
As I write the story, I get the sense of in storytelling, the impact and more sensitive information comes in the gap between the text and the image, like a sparkle of electricity between two wires, like the silence in a rhythm. Avoid the obvious, treat the reader as the sensitive intelligent person actually is.  #writing #artistsoninstagram #art #penguin #melancholy #graficnovel #therapist

“La calanque”, painting version. 
Acrylic on paper, 46x40,5 cm.
I'm very happy to tell you all I'm working on a exhibition that would take place in a few months. 
I love do traditional paintings, but in the last years my books have kept me busy with no more excuse to paint beyond the covers. So when we decided to go for the exhibition this beach picture come to my mind immediately, as I always wanted to do a painting version since I designed it for a book. This ideal place that looks like heaven to my is a very symbolic place to start this new adventure among brushes and canvas. 
More details about all it will be followed. 
#beach #heaven #painting #light #picoftheday #visdevart #artistsoninstagram #art

BLAST!
New cover special edition piece on Beaux Étés 1.
I wasn't really sure about this cover piece. For the first time in the series I worked on digital  color and I felt like fake all the time. ( The impostor fake syndrome is quite common on artists, so I went on with it anyway ). Luky me, I work with an incredible team that helps me in this kinds of situations where I'm not sure about what I'm doing. I want to special thanks my dears editor @ryun_reuchamps and designer Philippe Ravon, who helped me out on this. Thank you guys!
